               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. ROSE.</p>
               <p>The prisoner Johnson was <rs id="t17870912-28-verdict140" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17870912-28-verdict140" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870912-28-verdict140" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
               humbly recommended to mercy on account of his youth
            </rs> by the Jury; and also on the part of the parish of Hackney, who carried on the prosecution.</p>
